runs.comm: Full and flat, a low full-toss outside off. Clubbed back to the bowler
a touch of width outside off, and a good connection from Warner, but good cover at extra cover.
belted across the line, another fine connection, and an even better tumbling stop at mid-on
slower ball, patted into a gap at short cover, and Warner is away
well struck, into the gap at cover, and they jog through for another single
a swing and a miss, good line and length from Woakes, and that's a very tidy first over
a flowing drive, into the covers, but straight at the field. England have got their options covered so far
good delivery, just threatened to ghost away at the last minute, and Watson leaves his bat hanging limply as the ball skids by
blocked out to point with a full stride. Another single as Collingwood rushes in

a steepling chance! Way, way up into the air, and if this was the Telstra Dome, or whatever it's now called, that would have hit the roof. Right underneath the ball with that shot, but Bresnan at mid-on never looked like getting close as the ball swirled over his head
on the hips, tucked away fine
on the pads, and that's Australia's first boundary. Shahzad speared the ball wide, but Warner was alert to it and made good contact. The outfield can't deny him either
effortless, flowing strike. Full and straight, and Watson puts his full body weight through that lofted drive. Straight as you like, over the rope
open face, steered down to third man
boshed out to deep midwicket, but the sweeper is in place
punched into the covers off the back foot
a sliced slap, down towards third man, but it drops just short of Luke Wright ...
opens the stance, and that's a quality punched drive, up and over mid-on, and rocketing to the fence before the sweeper can intercept. A fine over for Australia
what a strike! On the toes, a lofted flick and that travels way over the head of deep midwicket. 89 metres, apparently, and bouncing off the boundary boards
fuller length, and Watson is drawn forward to push into the covers
driven again, into the covers
slower ball, well disguised, and Warner's attempted swipe is mistimed out to  short cover
bouncer, pretty well directed to be honest, but Warner was equal to it, helping round the corner and one bounce over the rope at fine leg
right up in the blockhole, and punched to mid-off to finish
crucial breakthrough. Full length again from Woakes, a flick across the line from Watson, but Morgan at deep square leg is in place to take the catch
down the leg-side
squared up a fraction by a shorter ball. Defended out to the leg side
good line and length, defended on off stump by the new batsman
mowed across the line. Not middled at all, but the bottom of the bat has enough meat to clear the long-on rope
slower ball again, dragged through midwicket
low full-toss, picks the gap at midwicket, and another more-than-decent over in the end for Australia
short and pulled calmly through midwicket
chopped out to point, and a bit of a scamper to make the non-striker's end
clipped out to midwicket
too short, and launched over point with an aggressive uppercut
slower ball, a violent swing and a miss. The ball trickles past the leg stump, but Paine had made room so no wide
excellent delivery, right into the blockhole, and punched into the covers
reverse sweep to start, but no connection
uses the feet well, and lofted handsomely over wide mid-on. The ball hits the rope as it lands
a touch early on that stroke, and chipped in the air through midwicket. But safe
round the wicket, and pushed off the back foot through extra cover
a swipe across the line, a massive steepler, Collingwood calls for it at short midwicket, steadies himself, fumbles the initial take, but clutches onto the rebound!
driven firmly but straight to short cover.
steered out to point, off the back foot
on the back foot, tapped to cover, and a quick single. Collingwood's shy hits the stumps, but he's home. Smart work though
heaved square, ungainly but effective, but good work on the rope from Morgan to save a single
lifter, very straight, and Hussey tries to loft that over the keeper's head, but can't make contact
chopped down to third man
low full toss, pumped down the ground to mid-off. Good over from Bresnan
looped up from round the wicket, defended to point
on the toes, flicked to short fine leg
worked to midwicket
sharp spin this time, as the ball gets tangled in Hussey's pads
weaved out to point with busy footwork.
dabbed in the air, dangerously close to Shahzad at short third man, who fields with a juggle on the bounce
Warner was looking for a leg-side wide there, but he accidentally got his pad in the way
tame end for Warner as he plays an unbalanced sliced loft down the ground, which Pietersen intercepts on the boundary's edge. Vital strike again from England, who are battling back now
attempted swish back past the bowler, but Yardy pounces in his followthrough
good flight, and White is beaten off the pitch
stabbed into space at mid-on, off the back foot
calm work from Yardy. A good length tweaker that White can only defend with a vertical bat
a bit of width, but Swann is bowling to his field as a cut shot is slapped towards deep third man
cracking delivery, genuine spin as White, the Victorian, is nailed on the back foot. Paul Reiffel, the umpire - another Victorian - sticks up the finger!
outside edge, poked through the gully region. That'll do
turned off the toes to square leg
another flick, but straight to midwicket. England are keeping things tight now
more sharp spin from an off-stump line. This is Test-match bowling from Swann
in the blockhole, driven back to the bowler
tapped with a closed face, down to long-on
smacked down to deep cover
on the toes, flicked out to deep midwicket
short this time, but it's a rare bad ball that is too eagerly accepted by Hussey. A greedy slap to deep midwicket, where Woakes makes no mistake!
good turn on a middle-stump line. Australia haven't scored a boundary for nearly six overs
waist-high full toss as Swann lets one slip with an aghast scream. But it's not costly
and there's the elusive boundary, a well-judged sweep through backward square
heaved into the leg-side
down on the sweep, but can't make proper contact
two strides down the wicket, and defended back to the bowler
another sharp offspinner to complete a fine spell from Swann. Smith tries to sweep but gets in a tangle
wide and walloped, out to deep point
worked into space at deep midwicket, good running brings two as the shy comes in
worked off the pads to square leg. No second run there
outside off, pushed out to deep cover
excellent running makes two from nothing as a push to mid-on finds the smallest of gaps, beyond Yardy's reach, and short of the in-rushing KP
Smith keeps the strike as Australia prepare for their final onslaught.
short, ballooning first delivery, but the ball takes an age to reach Smith's swipe. Which, of course, is the entire point
driven down to the covers
proper spin from Pietersen as Finch advances
off-line from Pietersen and that is firmly swept behind square
slow and wide, jabbed to third man
good finish to the over, on a good length and turning slowly. Defended to point
clipped to midwicket
on the toes, flicked very fine and they come back for the second
leg stump line again, backward square tidies up
open-faced drive, out to extra cover
very full length, dug out of the blockhole, fielded at mid-on
heroic mow to a wide delivery, but that one eludes the bat. Yardy finishes with the second 4-0-19-2 analysis of the evening. Top drawer
belted! in the slot, and clean over mid-off!
cracking delivery! A lifter on off stump, and beats the bat
very wide, left alone, but it's just inside the tramlines
a mow, but no contact
cracked hard, up and over the covers. Excellent shot
dot ball to finish. Not a bad recovery from KP in that over
slower ball, there might be a few of those. Full and straight and worked to mid-on
attempted yorker, tailing in from outside off, good delivery and even better fielding as Shahzad saves a certain four with a full-length dive at short third man
a leg-side waft, and Bell at short midwicket pounces to save the boundary. Sharp fielding as ever
slower-ball bouncer, and Finch top-edges that straight into his face! Lucky he's got a lid on ... good ball
another slower ball, guided straight to point
and another slower ball, another mow across the line, and a scrambled single as the shy comes in
cracking strike. Anticipating pace, and turned his stance inside-out to lift the ball Dilshan-style over fine leg!
bouncer, Finch charges down the track, top-edges a pull, which plugs at deep square leg! it's all happening, but these runs are vital
slow, slow, slow, bouncer, tennis-ball smash, straight back to the bowler. That was a genuine leg-break!
another slower ball, a cutter this time, another smash, and short cover crouches to intercept.
another slower ball, Collingwood tried to swoop at short cover, but the run was always on
another legbreak, too short, and that is belted across the line. Bresnan, the man in the deep, flails hopefully, but can't intercept! Valuable blow
what on earth happened there? Ah, O'Keefe was bowled, that's what. An attempted Dilscoop, but he just ends up looking like a Dil, as his leg bail is removed by a length ball
in the blockhole, flicked uppishly to deep square leg
waist-high full toss, clubbed out to midwicket, and they dash back for two. Bell's shy comes in on the bounce, which loses valuable seconds
another bosh across the line, picks the gap well, as two men converge to save the boundary
slower ball again, and that is a precious maiden fifty for the 24-year-old Victorian, Aaron Finch. Bill Lawry would be doing handstands, no doubt
smacked out to deep long on. Well played Finch, he's kept Australia afloat. England will need 148 to win. Exactly what they chased at Bridgetown in May, as it happens.
